# Samples

They are identified by `route path`

## Remove route

Remove path `/path/to/` and all its children routes:

```javascript
router.removeRoute('/path/to')
```

## Replace routes

Replace route `/path/to`:

```javascript
router.replaceRoutes([{
  path: '/path/to',
  component: NewComponent,
  // something else
}, {
  // more replacement
}])
```

### What problem does this feature solve?
If I just want to set a value for one state, I must code: 

```js
const state = {
     test : 1
}

const mutations = {
      setTest(state, value) {
            state.test = value
      }
}
```

I wrote or read most of the mutations are this kind of. So If `vuex` set default mutations for all states we will reduce most of the mutations set.

### What does the proposed API look like?

```js
const state = {
    test: 1
}

const actions = {
      async setTestWhenRequest(context) {
            let res = await axios.get('http://www.new-issue.vuejs.org')
            if ( res.code === 200) {
                  context.commit('$setTest', 2)
            }
      }
}
```

